headline: Clorox (NYSE:CLX) Beats Q3 Sales Expectations
summary: Consumer products giant Clorox (NYSE:CLX) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q3 CY2025, but sales fell by 18.9% year on year to $1.43 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.85 per share was 9.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Clorox’s System Change Dents Earnings, Sales
summary: The cleaning-products company’s first-quarter sales fell 19% to $1.43 billion as a result of shipment changes made in anticipation of an ERP system transition.
